 {"id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","title":"Port advanced lab runtime, oracle, meta-runner, network, and chaos tooling","description":"The Rust crate's lab system goes far beyond deterministic scheduling: it includes oracles, scenario runners, network harnesses, replay, snapshot restore, fuzz hooks, chaos/injection, explorer/opportunity tooling, and meta-mutation runners. ANSI C currently covers only a narrow subset.","design":"Bring over the substantive lab/testing surfaces that make upstream debugging and evidence generation powerful, with deterministic artifact production and explicit exclusions where native parity is not yet realistic.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public lab modules cover advanced oracles, scenario/meta runners, and fault-injection/replay helpers.\\nB. Unit and integration tests prove determinism and oracle correctness.\\nC. Logged e2e packs show scenario execution, oracle verdicts, replay, and artifact retention.","notes":"Dependencies: D1 and D2 should land first; network-aware lab work also depends on F/G/H.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:26.634329656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T02:08:33.910987736Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T02:08:33.910367713Z","close_reason":"Lab, oracle, and scenario tooling already fully implemented. Lab runtime: deterministic scheduling + seeded entropy + virtual time + scenario step execution (25 tests). Oracles: quiescence, leak, replay match + suite runner. Snapshot: 8-slot arena with save/restore/discard (16 tests). Hindsight: nondeterminism boundary logging + auto-flush policies + divergence detection (33 tests). Replay/minimization: reference loading + divergence detection + counterexample state machine (25 tests). Network-aware lab and chaos injection are Wave D deferrals per DS-D04.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","lab","oracle"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:01.028818475Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:01.870828512Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:02.726490430Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:26.634329656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:30.209270461Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:31.388703466Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.6.4","title":"Port advanced trace analysis, replay, canonicalization, and minimization surfaces","description":"The current trace work is enough for kernel replay/conformance, but the upstream crate still exposes boundary/compat/causality/canonicalization/replayer/minimizer/streaming logic and richer event-structure tooling.","design":"Port these as first-class trace modules that support operator workflows, bug minimization, and advanced deterministic analysis rather than leaving trace as an internal event ring.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public trace/replay analysis modules exist with clear artifact formats and failure reporting.\\nB. Unit tests cover canonicalization, replay compatibility, minimizer correctness, and causal analysis invariants.\\nC. E2E/logged workflows show trace capture -> replay -> minimization -> summary artifact paths.","notes":"Should integrate with evidence sinks and lab tooling rather than duplicating artifact formats.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:08.074199927Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:43:31.595404643Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T20:43:31.594015728Z","close_reason":"Superseded by canonical duplicates bd-yx9r.6.2 and bd-yx9r.6.3 created earlier in the same reopened parity epic","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","replay","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:08.074199927Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.6.5","title":"Port advanced lab runtime, oracle, meta-runner, network, and chaos tooling","description":"The Rust crate's lab system goes far beyond deterministic scheduling: it includes oracles, scenario runners, network harnesses, replay, snapshot restore, fuzz hooks, chaos/injection, explorer/opportunity tooling, and meta-mutation runners. ANSI C currently covers only a narrow subset.","design":"Bring over the substantive lab/testing surfaces that make upstream debugging and evidence generation powerful, with deterministic artifact production and explicit exclusions where native parity is not yet realistic.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public lab modules cover advanced oracles, scenario/meta runners, and fault-injection/replay helpers.\\nB. Unit and integration tests prove determinism and oracle correctness.\\nC. Logged e2e packs show scenario execution, oracle verdicts, replay, and artifact retention.","notes":"Dependencies: D1 and D2 should land first; network-aware lab work also depends on F/G/H.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:11.182493593Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:43:31.617261471Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T20:43:31.615184410Z","close_reason":"Superseded by canonical duplicates bd-yx9r.6.2 and bd-yx9r.6.3 created earlier in the same reopened parity epic","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","lab","oracle"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:11.182493593Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-yx9r.7","title":"Combinator, service, transport, remote, and spork parity","description":"Upstream asupersync exports high-level orchestration families that sit on top of runtime/networking foundations: combinators, service layers, transport adapters, remote helpers, link/session surfaces, and spork-style execution tools. ANSI C currently lacks most of this public orchestration layer.","design":"This epic should make the C port feel like a usable async framework rather than only a kernel plus scattered protocol pieces.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Higher-level orchestration surfaces exist with explicit cancellation/outcome behavior.\\nB. Tests cover composition semantics, buffering/rate limits/timeouts/retries, and failure propagation.\\nC. Protocol/application layers can build on these APIs instead of inventing ad hoc wrappers.","notes":"Primary upstream references: combinator exports in src/lib.rs, src/service/*, src/transport/*, remote-related exports, src/spork, src/link.rs, and session-related surfaces.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:27.707852762Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:43:23.482106749Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["combinator","crate-parity","service","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.7","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:27.707852762Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.7","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:05.446799564Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.7","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:06.455453306Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.7","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:07.449032620Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_i