 {"id":"bd-yx9r.7.1","title":"Port join/race/select/timeout/retry combinator surface","description":"ANSI C needs the real user-facing combinator layer promised by the upstream crate, not just ad hoc kernel helpers. This includes joins, races, selection, timeout wrappers, retry-ish composition, and explicit outcome aggregation semantics.","design":"Implement the combinators as stable public APIs with strong cancellation and ownership contracts, backed by law-style tests and realistic composition scenarios.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public combinator APIs exist and integrate with , cancellation, and scope rules.\\nB. Unit/property tests cover algebraic composition and loser-drain behavior.\\nC. Smoke scenarios demonstrate real multi-branch orchestration with detailed logs.","notes":"Depends on B and D.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:28.897979302Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-17T06:50:31.299963999Z","closed_at":"2026-03-17T06:50:31.299441641Z","close_reason":"Combinator surface now complete with cancel token, composition helpers, and algebraic laws. Added: (1) asx_cancel_token type with cooperative cancellation checking, (2) asx_race_timeout combinator (race + deadline), (3) asx_retry_timeout combinator (retry + overall deadline), (4) 9 algebraic law tests (identity, severity lattice, determinism, commutativity), (5) 3 composition tests (retry+race, join+pipeline, race+bracket). Total: 23 new tests + 94 existing = 117 combinator tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["combinator","crate-parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.7.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:03.560638360Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.7.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:04.423593418Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r